  "description": "Understanding unexpected bleeding outside your period.",
  "fullContent": "### What Is Spotting?\n\nSpotting refers to light vaginal bleeding that occurs outside of your normal menstrual period.\n\n### Common Causes\n\n• Ovulation\n• Birth control changes\n• Stress\n• Pregnancy implantation bleeding\n• Hormonal fluctuations\n• PCOS\n• Uterine polyps\n• Infections\n\n### When Spotting Is Usually Not Serious\n\nOccasional light spotting that resolves quickly may simply reflect hormonal changes.\n\n### When To Seek Medical Advice\n\nConsult a healthcare professional if spotting is frequent, heavy, painful, occurs after sex, or happens after menopause.\n\n### Key Takeaway\n\nA small amount of spotting can be normal, but repeated episodes deserve evaluation to rule out underlying conditions."
