  "description": "Why your breasts feel sore before menstruation.",
  "fullContent": "### Is Breast Tenderness Normal?\n\nYes. Many people experience breast tenderness during the luteal phase of the menstrual cycle.\n\n### Why It Happens\n\nHormones such as estrogen and progesterone fluctuate throughout the cycle. These changes can cause:\n\n• Swelling\n• Tenderness\n• Heaviness\n• Increased sensitivity\n\n### Common Symptoms\n\n• Soreness in both breasts\n• Increased sensitivity around nipples\n• Feeling of fullness\n• Symptoms improving after menstruation begins\n\n### When To Seek Medical Advice\n\nSpeak with a healthcare provider if you notice:\n\n• A new breast lump\n• One-sided pain only\n• Nipple discharge\n• Skin changes\n\n### Key Takeaway\n\nBreast tenderness before a period is a common PMS symptom caused by normal hormonal fluctuations."
