  "description": "Understanding cramps without bleeding.",
  "fullContent": "### Why Am I Cramping But Not Bleeding?\n\nMany people experience cramps even when their period hasn't started.\n\n### Possible Causes\n\n• Period is about to start\n• Delayed ovulation\n• Early pregnancy\n• Ovulation pain\n• Digestive issues\n• Endometriosis\n• Adenomyosis\n• Ovarian cysts\n\n### Could Pregnancy Cause Cramping?\n\nSome people experience mild cramping during early pregnancy as the uterus begins to adapt.\n\n### When To See A Doctor\n\nSeek medical attention if cramps are:\n\n• Severe\n• Sudden\n• Accompanied by fever\n• Associated with heavy bleeding\n• Persistent for several days\n\n### Key Takeaway\n\nCramps without a period can occur for many reasons, ranging from normal cycle changes to underlying medical conditions."
