  "description": "What cervical discharge may indicate when your period is delayed.",
  "fullContent": "### Is White Discharge Normal?\n\nIn many cases, yes.\n\nThe cervix naturally produces discharge throughout the menstrual cycle. Hormonal fluctuations can change its amount and appearance.\n\n### Possible Causes\n\n• Approaching menstruation\n• Delayed ovulation\n• Early pregnancy\n• Hormonal changes\n• Birth control use\n\n### Pregnancy Considerations\n\nSome individuals notice increased creamy white discharge during early pregnancy due to rising hormone levels.\n\n### When To Seek Medical Advice\n\nConsult a healthcare professional if discharge is accompanied by:\n\n• Strong odor\n• Itching\n• Burning\n• Green or yellow color\n• Pelvic pain\n\n### Key Takeaway\n\nWhite discharge alongside a late period is often linked to normal hormonal changes but can occasionally occur during early pregnancy."
